commit.message:
kern_start: Add Continuity Camera Unlocking

macOS Ventura implements an arbitrary CPUID check to determine whether Continuity Camera can start. This is primarily to validate HEVC support, however this has been determined to not be required. Machines as old as MacBook7,1 have been validated to work
